<p><b>Infotainment,</b> is "information-based media content or programming that also includes entertainment content in an effort to enhance popularity with audiences and consumers." <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> It is a neologistic <a href="/wiki/Portmanteau" title="Portmanteau">portmanteau</a> (information and entertainment), refers to a type of <a href="/wiki/Electronic_media" title="Electronic media">media</a> which provides a combination of information and entertainment. According to many dictionaries <sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> infotainment is always television, and the term is "mainly disapproving."<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> However, many self-described infotainment websites exist which provide a variety of functions and services. <sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
